<item>
            <title>[FLINK-20888] ContinuousFileReaderOperator should not close the output on close()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-20888</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently ContinuousFileReaderOperator would close the output on close(), if it is chained with more operators, it would also close the following operators before their endOfInput() is called (by default, we would call op1.endInput(), op1.close(), op2.endInput(), op2.close()... in order). This might cause some problems like in&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/r50a94aaea4fe25f3927a4274ea8272e6b76ecec8f3fe48d2566689bd%40%3Cuser.flink.apache.org%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/r50a94aaea4fe25f3927a4274ea8272e6b76ecec8f3fe48d2566689bd%40%3Cuser.flink.apache.org%3E&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
